node_modules
test
docs
scripts
.github
.git
.worktrees
.moat-ship-agent-*
worktree-agent-*
**/*.test.js
**/*.md
# ORDER-SENSITIVE — last matching rule wins, so these negations MUST stay below
# `docs` and `**/*.md` or they are inert. `!README.md` only rescues the ROOT
# readme, not nested ones: the docs pack's payload is AGENTS.md + CLAUDE.md, so
# without a negation the image gets a pack.json whose declared files are gone —
# loadPack throws and --fix silently offers no packs at all.
#
# `!templates/**` (not `!templates`) is deliberate and verified against a real
# build: docker only EVALUATES a negation for a path that is currently excluded.
# Nothing excludes the templates/ directory itself — only its .md files — so a
# bare `!templates` is never evaluated there, records no match, and cannot
# rescue the files beneath it. The glob matches each file path directly.
!README.md
!templates/**
# `rigscore explain <check>` reads docs/checks/<id>.md at runtime; only that
# subtree is read by shipped code, so the rest of docs/ stays out of the image.
# `docs/` IS excluded above, so this dir-form negation is evaluated and does
# propagate to the files below it.
!docs/checks
.rigscore-action-src
.DS_Store
coverage
.rigscore-state.json
.release-notes-*.md
